l-fast\n  loop_type: research\n  config.stopPolicy: convergence\n  research_topic: How should the sk-design skill and its five nested modes (interface, foundations, motion, audit, md-generator) smartly index, retrieve, and consume the ~1,290-style design-token library at .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/ (each folder = DESIGN.md + css-variables.css + tailwind-v4.css + design-tokens.json + source.md)? Investigate concretely: (1) retrieval substrate — a static committed index the modes read, a queryable tokens store, or on-demand grep over DESIGN.md; (2) which mode consumes what and how, including when to reference ONE real style vs synthesize across many; (3) an anti-slop discipline so output stays distinctive, never averaged into a generic middle; (4) tooling/index build + refresh; (5) risks (size, staleness, license/provenance). Rank utilization strategies by leverage vs build cost, each with concrete evidence citing sk-design files/patterns and the styles corpus.\n  config.maxIterations: 10\n  config.convergenceThreshold: 0.05\nThe step_resolve_artifact_root step will bind artifact_dir to .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol via the\nconfig.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir override — do NOT run the resolveArtifactRoot node\ncommand; bind artifact_dir directly to the override value.\n\nRun phase_init, phase_main_loop (to legal convergence OR config.maxIterations, whichever comes first), and phase_synthesis.\nWrite all outputs to .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol. Do not touch any path outside .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol.\n\nWhen complete, output a single line: FANOUT_LINEAGE_COMPLETE:sol\n","exit":0,"truncated":false},"title":"pgrep -fl \"fanout-sol-\"","time":{"start":1784371393573,"end":1784371393574}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03bf0c16f5029b3