{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1784371400519,"sessionID":"ses_08b2f9e0bffesj9FY7WWisVCBE","part":{"id":"prt_f74d2cf4400137hRkNea1J2t9l","messageID":"msg_f74d2c00d001NXiD0Ly3LHobex","sessionID":"ses_08b2f9e0bffesj9FY7WWisVCBE","snapshot":"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1784371411124,"sessionID":"ses_08b2f9e0bffesj9FY7WWisVCBE","part":{"id":"prt_f74d2f10a001YiSqzCXRKD50Cy","messageID":"msg_f74d2c00d001NXiD0Ly3LHobex","sessionID":"ses_08b2f9e0bffesj9FY7WWisVCBE","type":"text","text":"A live earlier detached lineage still owns the same lock and is completing synthesis in the exact target directory. To avoid two writers corrupting append-only state, I’m waiting for that owner to exit, then I’ll validate the resulting packet before returning the lineage completion marker.","time":{"start":1784371409162,"end":1784371411117},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_033eba2ddd5bac31016a5b58d0c8c481919b84251c14a47573","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784371441494,"sessionID":"ses_08b2f9e0bffesj9FY7WWisVCBE","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_G0KC0b6QoktNsik2v4riqM92","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"sleep 30 && ps -p 36344 -o pid=,stat=,etime=,command= || true","workdir":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public","timeout":120000},"output":"36344 Ss   01:20:34 opencode run --model openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast --format json --pure --dir /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public --variant xhigh You are orchestrating the deep-research workflow YAML as a detached fan-out lineage.\\012This is an explicit parallel-detached OpenCode lineage, not a self-invocation of the parent session.\\012Use the separate lineage directory and session id below as the detached state boundary.\\012\\012\\012Read .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md and execute the research loop with these parameters:\\012  spec_folder: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization\\012  config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol\\012  session_id: fanout-sol-1784366607889-1j7alg\\012  executor: cli-opencode model=openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast\\012  loop_type: research\\012  config.stopPolicy: convergence\\012  research_topic: How should the sk-design skill and its five nested modes (interface, foundations, motion, audit, md-generator) smartly index, retrieve, and consume the ~1,290-style design-token library at .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/ (each folder = DESIGN.md + css-variables.css + tailwind-v4.css + design-tokens.json + source.md)? Investigate concretely: (1) retrieval substrate — a static committed index the modes read, a queryable tokens store, or on-demand grep over DESIGN.md; (2) which mode consumes what and how, including when to reference ONE real style vs synthesize across many; (3) an anti-slop discipline so output stays distinctive, never averaged into a generic middle; (4) tooling/index build + refresh; (5) risks (size, staleness, license/provenance). Rank utilization strategies by leverage vs build cost, each with concrete evidence citing sk-design files/patterns and the styles corpus.\\012  config.maxIterations: 10\\012  config.convergenceThreshold: 0.05\\012The step_resolve_artifact_root step will bind artifact_dir to .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol via the\\012config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir override — do NOT run the resolveArtifactRoot node\\012command; bind artifact_dir directly to the override value.\\012\\012Run phase_init, phase_main_loop (to legal convergence OR config.maxIterations, whichever comes first), and phase_synthesis.\\012Write all outputs to .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol. Do not touch any path outside .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol.\\012\\012When complete, output a single line: FANOUT_LINEAGE_COMPLETE:sol\n","metadata":{"output":"36344 Ss   01:20:34 opencode run --model openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast --format json --pure --dir /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public --variant xhigh You are orchestrating the deep-research workflow YAML as a detached fan-out lineage.\\012This is an explicit parallel-detached OpenCode lineage, not a self-invocation of the parent session.\\012Use the separate lineage directory and session id below as the detached state boundary.\\012\\012\\012Read .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md and execute the research loop with these parameters:\\012  spec_folder: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization\\012  config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol\\012  session_id: fanout-sol-1784366607889-1j7alg\\012  executor: cli-opencode model=openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast\\012  loop_type: research\\012  config.stopPolicy: convergence\\012  research_topic: How should the sk-design skill and its five nested modes (interface, foundations, motion, audit, md-generator) smartly index, retrieve, and consume the ~1,290-style design-token library at .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/ (each folder = DESIGN.md + css-variables.css + tailwind-v4.css + design-tokens.json + source.md)? Investigate concretely: (1) retrieval substrate — a static committed index the modes read, a queryable tokens store, or on-demand grep over DESIGN.md; (2) which mode consumes what and how, including when to reference ONE real style vs synthesize across many; (3) an anti-slop discipline so output stays distinctive, never averaged into a generic middle; (4) tooling/index build + refresh; (5) risks (size, staleness, license/provenance). Rank utilization strategies by leverage vs build cost, each with concrete evidence citing sk-design files/patterns and the styles corpus.\\012  config.maxIterations: 10\\012  config.convergenceThreshold: 0.05\\012The step_resolve_artifact_root step will bind artifact_dir to .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol via the\\012config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir override — do NOT run the resolveArtifactRoot node\\012command; bind artifact_dir directly to the override value.\\012\\012Run phase_init, phase_main_loop (to legal convergence OR config.maxIterations, whichever comes first), and phase_synthesis.\\012Write all outputs to .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol. Do not touch any path outside .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol.\\012\\012When complete, output a single line: FANOUT_LINEAGE_COMPLETE:sol\n","exit":0,"truncated":false},"title":"sleep 30 && ps -p 36344 -o pid=,stat=,etime=,command= || true","time":{"start":1784371441490,"end":1784371441493}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_033eba2ddd5bac31016a5b58d2f42481919138081ff9baff93"}},"id":"prt_f74d2f8af001FMstGVGzTUY7Rf","sessionID":"ses_08b2f9e0bffesj9FY7WWisVCBE","messageID":"msg_f74d2c00d001NXiD0Ly3LHobex"}}
